++THIS MAP IS FINISHED, CHECK OUT THE FINAL VERSION HERE++ This is a final beta. I'll be compiling the true final version in about a week, after taking suggestions and acting upon them. This is still a fully functional surf map, with 4 levels and 1 finish. All players spawn with an m3 (pump shotty) and a knife in the spawn-kill proof spawn area (see screenshot D). The surf ramps resemble a double helix which span 4 areas. Mayhem and fragging ensues on the ramps and the jail. Players are teleported to jail with weapons and locations equivalent to how far they got, heres that list:
Fail on first level - Bottom of jail with only knife. Fail on second level - 2nd tier of jail with glock and knife. Fail on third level - 3rd tier of jail with deagle and knife. Fail on fourth level - 4th tier of jail with m4 and knife. Beat fourth level - Top of jail with Awp and knife.
Also included (in the bspzip, only one file ;P) are some custom decals I made for the spawn. Enjoy!

A surf map inspired by the ancient greek text, Ovid's Metamorphoses: Daedalus and Icarus.

Surf through a four-leveled double helix, with enemy shotgun shells hot on your trail. If your wings fail you and you don't make it all the way, you spawn in a jail, referenced as "hell" by the beta testers, with a position and gun worthy of your ability. The tier of guns are as follows; knife, glock, deagle, m4a1, AWP.

Included is a NON mat_fullbright map (pretty lighting) and some custom decals in the spawn (including the famous Icarus drawing from the album "Led Zeppelin IV"). Those who don't make it to the end can escape from jail through a set of doors, however, they don't open right away. It takes 80 seconds for the knife-area to be "freed", and each level above that becomes earlier in 20 second increments (play the map, you'll understand).

Enjoy, if I get good feedback I may make other "non-standard" surf maps in the future.

Teeth: This map takes the idea of Surf_skyworld_unlimited and applies it to every dimension. This map was kind of a test run of the idea and has some bugs. I'm going to release a DM version soon (HOLD YOUR PANTS ON PAPER-CUT).
This map will require tons of strategy as you can attack from any angle at all, so keep your guard up! It's good to note that you never leave the same sector, as you simply teleport back to the other side when you go to the next one. This means that jumping off the bottom will have you attacking from the top. WHEN YOU DIE HERE YOU DIE IN RL. This map is Xbox, maybe even ps3, hueg (27 megabytes) so if you want this baby, you need fast dl. I know, I know, but to create a decent effect we needed to have many copies in the skybox, making a small map enormous. Decent fps, though.

Roosta: The design is based off of surf_elk_boost, created by +ELK+ stpwned, and as such we wish to thank him for the design. To those of you who wonder about the name, don't. You wouldn't understand t (especially so if you are a civil engineer). It both sounds cool and means something, but just worry about the sounds cool part.

SURF_HYPER
==================

surf_hyper is a staged skillsurf map made by Helix. It contains 5 stages which are easy to medium difficulty.

This map is mainly designed for timer servers, therefore there is no jail nor a timer in the map.

There is also a bonus, which contains 4 stages. All 4 stages must be no-failed in order to complete it. When you fail, you will go to the bonus spawn where you can either retry or exit.

Bonus can be activated by pressing "E" while in the out-of-space zone in stage 1. You can enter it by landing on top of the spawnbox in stage 2.

Enjoy the map.

SURF_HURRICANE

By WikmaN.

This is one of my first maps. As you can see, it's inspired by surf_greatriver and surf_machine.

I recommend sv_airaccelerate 100 on it.

JAIL

To get out of jail, you take a grenade from the table, and throw it inside the box at the ''pyramid'', Behind you a door will open and you are free!

TOP

To get to top, you simply go with one of the two ways until you get to the teleport room. Go into the ''Top'' teleporter and you are at top! In top, you can get weapons and kill people in spawn.

JAILTOP

To get to jailtop, i've hidden two ways, one in each surf-way. Im not gonna tell you where, but think like this: On the way that you go up in a ladder, you get to jail top in a ladder (a invisable) and on the way that you go down to the tele room, you go down to jailtop.

OTHER SECRETS

I've hidden two rooms with awp and autosnipers, find them yourself.

In jailtop, there is a teleport that requires a code. You can try to guess the code but be careful, if you press the wrong button, something bad might happen!

TIPS & TRICKS

Try to find your own way, so you will get to the place you want faster!

At the platform with guns, bunnyhop there and you will get speed!

The top of the hole-thingy in the left way looks like a good sniper spot to me.

Creds goes to Skurt, Zero and Glados for beta testing it!


If Ill make a v2, there will be ligtning

                                                      Happy surfing!

A 6 stage skill map based off the hit map surf_hydrogen.

The map is on a 5 minute timer, and when it expires (if noone beats the map) people will be teleported to jail and receive the following weapons (different for t and ct)

lv1- knife
lv2- pistol
lv3- tmp/mac10
lv4- galil/famas
lv5- ak/m4
lv6- awp

if beaten, the winner will be taken to an area and have a choice of para, or blades.

max. 36 players

SPECIAL THANKS TO KNIFE FOR THE JAIL AND HELP ALONG THE WAY <33

thanks to intox. clan

thanks to zalos for nofalldmg fixing

Players start on opposite sides of the spawn facing different directions making it very difficult to jump into spawn.

There are weapon spawns for every riffle and Machine gun strewn about on the map

There is a port to the top after a very easy surf.

From there it breaks up to noob and pro surf.

At the end of noob there is a port to top, a machine gun spawner, and a teleporter to the upper portion of jail (see screenshot) which holds the release switch to jail.

At the end of pro there is a port to top, a low gravity spawner, and a port to underneath the jail which holds the kill switch. Also, the pro finish overlooks the noob finish with a 1 way wall.
